{{meat}}

'''Pepperoni''' is a popular type of [[Cookbook:Salami|salami]], and [[Cookbook:Cuisine of Italy|Italian]] [[Cookbook:Fermentation|fermented]] sausage. It usually consists of pork, beef, and spices, and is commonly used as a pizza topping and as a snack.

The Italian word ''"peperoni"'' means sweet bell peppers or capsicums.

{{wikipedia|Pepperoni}}

{{cookstub}}

[[Category:Meat and poultry|Pepperoni]]

{{ingredient}}
[[Image:Long hot dog in bun.jpg|right|thumb|Hot dog with ketchup and mustard]]

A '''hot dog''' (also known as a '''frankfurter''') is a variant on a sandwich, or the [[Cookbook:Sausage|sausage]] inside, usually made of [[Cookbook:Beef|beef]].  In consists of a [[Cookbook:Bun|bun]] and a frankfurter sausage, and usually has a variety of toppings, including [[Cookbook:Ketchup|ketchup]], [[Cookbook:Mustard|mustard]], [[Cookbook:Relish|relish]], [[Cookbook:Onion|onion]]s, and [[Cookbook:Pickle|pickle]]s. [[Cookbook:Cheese|Cheese]] is also a popular topping for Hot Dogs. Hot Dogs range in size, and can be up to a foot long.

When wrapped in bacon and deep-fried, it is known as a Danger dog when served with [[Cookbook:Mayonnaise |mayonnaise ]] and as a [[Cookbook:Jersey_breakfast_dog|Jersey breakfast dog]] when served on a fried egg and cheese. [http://www.esquire.com/print-this/60things0507]

{{wikipedia|Hot dog}}
<br clear='all'>
{{cookstub}}

[[hy:Եփութուխ:Հոթ դոգ]]

This is a guide to essential oils that are used in aromatherapy, their properties and ailments that they can treat. Some essential oils present specific dangers to pregnant women or people with certain medical conditions. If you are pregnant or have a medical condition, always consult a doctor before trying aromatherapy.
