AppletMagic is targeting the Java Virtual Machine and
uses word sizes of the JVM, i.e. up to 64 bits.
This includes a mapping to short and long IEEE floating point types.

As with other compilers there is no actual package Standard,
the information is provided in system packages.
The System_Name is <code>Jcode</code>. Some definitions
are


    Min_Int               {{Ada/delimiter|:}} {{Ada/keyword|constant}} {{Ada/delimiter|1=:=}}{{Ada/operator|-}}2{{Ada/operator|**}}63{{Ada/delimiter|;}}
    Max_Int               {{Ada/delimiter|:}} {{Ada/keyword|constant}} {{Ada/delimiter|1=:=}} 2{{Ada/operator|**}}63 {{Ada/operator|-}} 1{{Ada/delimiter|;}}

    Max_Binary_Modulus    {{Ada/delimiter|:}} {{Ada/keyword|constant}} {{Ada/delimiter|1=:=}} 2{{Ada/operator|**}}64{{Ada/delimiter|;}}
    Max_Nonbinary_Modulus {{Ada/delimiter|:}} {{Ada/keyword|constant}} {{Ada/delimiter|1=:=}} 2{{Ada/operator|**}}63 {{Ada/operator|-}} 1{{Ada/delimiter|;}}

    Max_Base_Digits       {{Ada/delimiter|:}} {{Ada/keyword|constant}} {{Ada/delimiter|1=:=}} 15{{Ada/delimiter|;}}
    Max_Digits            {{Ada/delimiter|:}} {{Ada/keyword|constant}} {{Ada/delimiter|1=:=}} 15{{Ada/delimiter|;}}

